Betty Friedan, a pioneer of the feminist movement, passed away at 85 due to heart failure.
Her groundbreaking book, "The Feminine Mystique," challenged societal norms and sparked a revolution for women's rights.
Friedan's legacy lives on through the progress made for women's equality.
Despite facing criticism for her past, Friedan's impact on gender equality remains undeniable.
Her work continues to inspire and empower women globally.
Friedan's dedication to challenging gender inequities paved the way for future generations of feminists.
Her contributions to the feminist movement will always be remembered and celebrated.
